"The Station Information, Security Systems Technician role involves working on Network Rail London Major Stations on a range of Telecoms equipment.The role will require you to undertaking faulting and maintenance activities with Customer Information Systems, Clocks, Passenger Help Points and Public Address systems.You will be part of a small telecoms team based at London Victoria Station, rostered to work a combination of days and nights shifts. There is an on call commitment and a large percentage of the work will include working at height. Any experience of working with audio/visual equipment and/or IT networking would be beneficial."